      "HI, I created a connection pool implementation for Java driver. It wraps connections and provides them in a round-robin fashion, creating new connections as needed. It supports connecting to multiple cluster nodes.\r\n```\r\nquery.run() // use the global pool\r\nquery.run(pool) // use the pool and automatically lease/return the connection when done\r\nquery.run(connection) // the legacy way\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is the basic test: https://github.com/PeterKnego/rethinkdb/blob/connection_pool/drivers/java/src/test/java/com/rethinkdb/FixedConnectionPoolTest.java"
